The '''Bantha Graveyard''' on [[Roon/Legends|Roon]] was the site of countless [[Bantha/Legends|bantha]] skeletons. It was here that [[Oggem Baobab|"Old Ogger" Baobab]] lived for sixty years, hoarding [[Roonstone]]s until his great nephew, [[Mungo Baobab]] arrived in the company of [[C-3PO/Legends|C-3PO]] and [[R2-D2/Legends|R2-D2]].

Similar to other planets, the closely-knit family units of the bantha result in unique social behavior. On Roon, aging members of a herd slowly make their way to the site of the graveyard, where they lay down to die amongst the remnants of their ancestors. It was here, among the skeletons, that horrific creatures were rumored to exist, preying upon the dying banthas and any travelers brave - or foolish - enough to set out across the wind-swept plains.

Notably, the Bantha Graveyard was not only the resting place of these deceased beasts, but also the site of numerous downed ships, from [[Starfighter/Legends|starfighters]] to [[Freighter/Legends|freighters]]. Scientists have theorized that this has something to do with the interference of Roon's event horizon with navigational systems, and late in the [[Galactic Civil War/Legends|Galactic Civil War]], the area above the graveyard was designated a no-fly zone.

